  "idea": "Biosignature-By-Design: End-to-end JWST vetting for habitable Earth-like worlds",
  "idea_description": "This work builds an end-to-end inference pipeline combining transit detection, machine learning anomaly vetting, atmospheric retrieval, comparative abiotic baselines across multi-planet systems, and habitability uncertainty models. The pipeline is trained and tested on JWST-era low-SNR exoplanet spectra, prioritizing terrestrial worlds with Earth-like habitable-zone conditions. It flags abiotic explanations, stellar contamination, and retrieval degeneracies while quantifying uncertainties in biosignature attribution. The goal is to identify candidate terrestrial worlds that are both spectroscopically habitable and statistically unlikely to host false positive biosignatures.",
